---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { config } from '../config';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookie Policy - BuildWorkPro"
  description="How BuildWorkPro uses cookies and similar technologies on its platform."
  noindex
>
  <Header />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="mb-12">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-brand-600 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Legal</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 tracking-tight">Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-400">
          Effective Date: April 9, 2026 &middot; Last Updated: June 10, 2026
        </p>
      </div>

      <div
        class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-headings:font-semibold prose-headings:tracking-tight prose-a:text-brand-600"
      >
        <p>
          This Cookie Policy (&ldquo;Policy&rdquo;) explains how BuildWorkPro LLC
          (&ldquo;BuildWorkPro,&rdquo; &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;us,&rdquo; or &ldquo;our&rdquo;)
          uses cookies and similar client-side storage technologies on the BuildWorkPro platform and
          marketing website (collectively, the &ldquo;Platform&rdquo;). This Policy should be read
          in conjunction with our <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>1. What Are Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files that are placed on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile
          phone) by a website when you visit it. Cookies enable the website to recognize your
          device, maintain session state, and store your preferences. They are widely used to make
          websites function correctly, function more efficiently, and provide information to site
          operators.
        </p>
        <p>
          In addition to traditional cookies, this Policy also covers the use of browser local
          storage (localStorage) and session storage (sessionStorage), which serve similar purposes
          but have different technical characteristics.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Cookies We Use</h2>
        <p>
          BuildWorkPro employs a minimal, privacy-respecting approach to cookies. We categorize our
          cookies as follows:
        </p>

        <h3>2.1 Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies are essential for the Platform to function and cannot be disabled without
          rendering core features inoperable. Under applicable privacy laws, including the EU
          ePrivacy Directive (2002/58/EC as amended) and the UK Privacy and Electronic
          Communications Regulations (PECR), no consent is required for strictly necessary cookies.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Cookie / Storage</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>connect.sid</code></td>
                <td
                  >Session authentication &mdash; maintains your logged-in state as you navigate the
                  Platform. Contains a cryptographically signed session identifier; does not contain
                  your password or personal data in plaintext.</td
                >
                <td>Expires after 24 hours of inactivity or 30 days maximum.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>CSRF token</td>
                <td
                  >Cross-site request forgery protection &mdash; ensures that form submissions and
                  API requests originate from the BuildWorkPro application and not from a malicious
                  third-party site.</td
                >
                <td>Per session.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Tenant context</td>
                <td
                  >Identifies the organization you are currently operating within in our
                  multi-tenant environment, ensuring that data requests are scoped to your
                  organization.</td
                >
                <td>Per session.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>2.2 Functional / Preference Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies and local storage entries remember your settings and interface choices to
          provide a more consistent user experience. They are set under the lawful basis of
          legitimate interest and do not track you across other websites.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Cookie / Storage</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td>Theme preference</td>
                <td>Stores your light or dark mode selection.</td>
                <td>Persistent (localStorage).</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>Language / locale</td>
                <td>Stores your preferred language and date/number format settings.</td>
                <td>Persistent (localStorage).</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td>UI state</td>
                <td
                  >Remembers interface preferences such as sidebar collapsed/expanded state, table
                  column visibility, and sort order.</td
                >
                <td>Persistent (localStorage).</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>bwp-cookies-accepted</code> / <code>bwp-cookies-declined</code></td>
                <td
                  >Records the choice you made in the cookie consent banner on the marketing site,
                  so we do not ask again and can honor your decision on every page.</td
                >
                <td>Persistent (localStorage).</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>2.3 Analytics &amp; Advertising Cookies (Consent-Based, Marketing Site Only)</h3>
        <p>
          The BuildWorkPro <strong>marketing website</strong> uses Google Analytics 4 to understand how
          visitors find and use our pages, and the <strong>Meta (Facebook) Pixel</strong> to measure the
          performance of our advertising and to show relevant ads to people who have visited the site.
          These cookies and similar identifiers are
          <strong>not loaded by default</strong>: for Google Analytics we use Google Consent Mode v2
          with every signal denied, and the Meta Pixel script is not loaded at all, until you click
          &ldquo;Accept&rdquo; in the cookie banner. If you decline, or simply ignore the banner,
          neither the Google Analytics nor the Meta Pixel script loads and none of these cookies are
          set. You can change your choice at any time via the &ldquo;Cookie settings&rdquo; link in
          the footer.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table>
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Cookie</th>
                <th>Purpose</th>
                <th>Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><code>_ga</code></td>
                <td
                  >Set by Google Analytics (only after you accept) to distinguish unique visitors.</td
                >
                <td>Up to 2 years.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>_ga_*</code></td>
                <td
                  >Set by Google Analytics (only after you accept) to maintain session state for our
                  measurement property.</td
                >
                <td>Up to 2 years.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>_fbp</code></td>
                <td
                  >Set by the Meta Pixel (only after you accept) to identify browsers for ad
                  measurement and delivery.</td
                >
                <td>Up to 3 months.</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><code>fr</code> / <code>_fbc</code></td>
                <td
                  >Set or read by Meta (only after you accept) for advertising attribution and
                  retargeting when you arrive from or interact with a Meta ad.</td
                >
                <td>Up to 3 months.</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p>
          None of these cookies are used inside the BuildWorkPro application itself. For details on
          how these third parties process data, see
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >Google&rsquo;s Privacy Policy</a
          >
          and
          <a
            href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Meta&rsquo;s Privacy Policy</a
          >.
        </p>

        <h3>2.4 Cookies We Do Not Use</h3>
        <p>We do not deploy any of the following:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Advertising cookies without consent:</strong> The Meta Pixel described in Section
            2.3 is the only advertising/retargeting technology we use, and it loads strictly after you
            accept. We do not use any advertising or conversion-tracking cookies before consent, and we
            do not use other ad networks&rsquo; tags (e.g., Google Ads remarketing, LinkedIn Insight Tag).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Session recording or heat-mapping tools:</strong> We do not use Hotjar, FullStory,
            or any similar session replay service.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Social media widget cookies:</strong> We do not embed social media widgets, share
            buttons, or login plugins that set third-party tracking cookies.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p>
          The BuildWorkPro marketing site loads typefaces from Google Fonts via a preconnect
          directive. When your browser requests font files from Google&rsquo;s servers, Google may
          receive your IP address and set cookies in accordance with its own privacy practices. For
          details, see <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Google&rsquo;s Privacy Policy</a
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          We use <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong> on our public forms (such as the contact form)
          to distinguish humans from bots without showing CAPTCHAs. Turnstile may set or read cookies
          and similar identifiers strictly for security and bot-mitigation purposes. This is a strictly
          necessary security function; see
          <a
            href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare&rsquo;s Privacy Policy</a
          > for details.
        </p>
        <p>
          We use the <strong>Meta (Facebook) Pixel</strong> on the marketing site for advertising measurement
          and retargeting. As described in Section 2.3, it loads only after you accept in the cookie banner;
          see
          <a
            href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Meta&rsquo;s Privacy Policy</a
          >.
        </p>
        <p>
          Other than Google Fonts, Cloudflare Turnstile, and the consent-based Google Analytics and
          Meta Pixel described above, no third-party service deployed on the Platform sets cookies
          in your browser.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Legal Basis for Cookie Use</h2>
        <p>Our use of cookies is grounded in the following legal bases:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Strictly necessary cookies (Section 2.1):</strong> Exempt from consent requirements
            under the EU ePrivacy Directive, UK PECR, and analogous legislation, as they are essential
            for the provision of the service you have explicitly requested.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Functional cookies (Section 2.2):</strong> Set under the lawful basis of legitimate
            interest (GDPR Art. 6(1)(f)), as they serve the purpose of improving your user experience
            without processing data in a manner that overrides your fundamental rights. You may disable
            these by clearing your browser&rsquo;s local storage at any time.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics &amp; advertising cookies (Section 2.3):</strong> Set only with your prior
            consent (GDPR Art. 6(1)(a) and the ePrivacy consent requirement), given through the cookie
            banner. You may withdraw consent at any time via the &ldquo;Cookie settings&rdquo; link in
            the footer; the Google Analytics and Meta Pixel scripts are not loaded unless and until you
            accept.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. How to Manage Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          You may view, manage, and delete cookies through your browser&rsquo;s privacy or security
          settings. Most modern browsers offer the following controls:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>View and delete individual cookies and local storage entries;</li>
          <li>Block all cookies or cookies from specific domains;</li>
          <li>Distinguish between first-party and third-party cookies;</li>
          <li>Automatically clear cookies and site data when you close the browser.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>Important:</strong> Disabling strictly necessary cookies (Section 2.1) will prevent
          you from authenticating and using the BuildWorkPro application. Clearing functional cookies
          (Section 2.2) will reset your preferences to defaults but will not affect your ability to log
          in.
        </p>
        <p>Instructions for common browsers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings &gt; Privacy and Security &gt; Cookies and other
            site data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong> Settings &gt; Privacy &amp; Security &gt; Cookies and Site
            Data
          </li>
          <li><strong>Apple Safari:</strong> Preferences &gt; Privacy &gt; Manage Website Data</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Settings &gt; Cookies and site permissions &gt; Manage and
            delete cookies and site data
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          If we introduce new categories of cookies or materially change how we use existing
          cookies, we will update this Policy and notify users where required by law. Material
          changes will be communicated through the Platform or by email. The &ldquo;Last
          Updated&rdquo; date at the top of this page will reflect the most recent revision.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Contact Information</h2>
        <p>If you have questions about our use of cookies or this Policy, please contact us:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Privacy Inquiries:</strong>
            <a href={`mailto:${config.email.privacy}`}>{config.email.privacy}</a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Web:</strong>
            <a href="/contact/">{config.siteUrl.replace('https://', '')}/contact/</a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
